"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786797","Home Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>Ministerial approval for the Intoximeter EC/IR breath analysis device was granted in 2005 by the then Home Office Parliamentary Under Secretary of State, the late Paul Goggins.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-11-20T08:09:07.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786797/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/786797/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-10","Breathalysers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which Minister of her Department personally approved by seal and signature the Intoximeter EC/IR breath analysis device in June 2005 for use by police forces in the UK.","false","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","112309"
